→ **Token is automatically stripped out**

**3. If I don't reply HEARTBEAT_OK:**
→ **Nothing bad happens!** Just unacknowledged, may retry

---

## Key Insight

**Nothing breaks if I don't reply HEARTBEAT_OK.** It's just a check-in mechanism.

**The instruction should be clearer:**
> "Active user instructions always take precedence. If you have assigned work, execute it. Only reply HEARTBEAT_OK when genuinely idle with no tasks."

Your explicit instructions ("update docs, tell me when done") should override the generic heartbeat! 🦞

